INSERT INTO `experiences` VALUES (1,'','[Culture Tourism Festival] Chungjang Festival of Memories 2021','Asia Culture Center and the entire area of Dong-gu, Gwangju','2021-11-03 00:00:00','2021-11-07 00:00:00','Chungjang-ro, a downtown representing Gwangju, is a unique street where a long history and rapid change coexist. Every October, the Chungjang Festival is held to make use of the characteristics of Chungjang-ro. In the ‘Chungjang Parade,’ the biggest highlight of the festival, 13 districts in Gwangju participate in parades with different themes, and various parades such as military and police parades, movie concept parades, and Asian national parades are held non-stop. In addition, a theme street of memories that reproduces the appearance of Chungjang-ro in the 70s and 80s will be created. You can have a pleasant retro experience, such as drinking tea at an old-fashioned coffee shop or taking nice black-and-white photos at a black and white photo studio.','https://cdn.ftoday.co.kr/news/photo/202109/223852_223429_5512.jpg'),(2,'','Suncheon Food and Arts Festival','Suncheon UD Street, Okcheonside Culture Street','2021-11-12 00:00:00','2021-11-13 00:00:00','Suncheon citizens participate in food stalls, Poape Market, Okcheonside water stage, and food trucks at Suncheon Moon Night Night Market to provide various food and attractions to Suncheon citizens in late autumn in November.',''),(3,'','Naju Cultural Heritage Night trip','Naju Eupseong area (Geumseonggwan ~ Seoseongmun)','2021-11-12 00:00:00','2021-11-14 00:00:00','Ancient historical and cultural city, Naju Cultural Heritage Night Trip (夜行) The essence of historical and cultural experience to enjoy as cultural assets, including Geumseonggwan, Najuhyanggyo, Jeongsuru, and Pastoral Naeah in Naju-eupseong area, etc. to offer','https://naju-culturenight.kr/html/images/sub0101_img01.jpg'),(4,'','Gwangju World Kimchi Festival','Gwangju Kimchi Town Event Hall','2021-10-29 00:00:00','2021-11-14 00:00:00','Enjoy our proud culture of Kimjang as a festival A festival to meet delicious Gwangju Kimchi with good ingredients and recipes from masters','https://postfiles.pstatic.net/MjAyMTEwMjVfNjEg/MDAxNjM1MTQ0MjQxMDc5.BiZVTu6JDiHg8NTOT2WLpBAAMymyLRiziTvwX3AUJFAg.13MvYc1MkiAcwUgDSkdbozOEyU57RhBbONMzsaZfZ4Ag.JPEG.dodreamgj/2.jpg?type=w966'),(5,'','2021 Atrts & Creative Technology Showcase','National Asia Culture Center ACC Creation,Space 1','2021-08-18 00:00:00','2021-11-14 00:00:00','The kinetic media platform 《Floating Frames》 is a system that combines a robot arm and a display, and provides a differentiated experience from existing video screenings by capturing various video creations through robot motion and three kinetic displays.','https://www.acc.go.kr/resources/upload/1228/20211014164029_759362720.gif'),(6,'','Adorable big brother ','Asia Culture Center ACC Creation, Space 6','2021-08-13 00:00:00','2021-11-14 00:00:00','The COVID-19 pandemic is penetrating the world where there is controversy over the state\'s surveillance and control for safety and invasion of personal privacy. The 2021 ACC Regional Asian Artist Exhibition <Dear Big Brother: About Never Be Alone Again> delivers the contrast of our lives where the Panopticon and the Synopticon coexist from the perspective of Asian artists. Through the colorful works of artists based in Gwangju and Asia, we explore the possibility of a new standard for the public interest and personal dignity of today\'s society that cannot but coexist with COVID-19, and discuss the reality of never being alone again. It provides a forum for public debate.','https://www.acc.go.kr/resources/upload/1228/20211014161248_1246632832.gif'),(7,'','Order Beyond Distortion','Outdoor space in the main building of the City Museum of Art','2021-11-10 00:00:00','2021-11-14 00:00:00','2021 Gwangju Museum of Art International Residency Result Presentation [Order Beyond Distortion] was inspired by Friedrich Nietzsche (1844-1900)\'s last book, \'Ecce Homo (Look at this Man, 1908)\'. planned. Written in the last years of Nietzsche\'s schizophrenia, this book is a kind of confession that the author gives to the reader by looking back and reinterpreting his achievements and achievements. Artists Hyung-sook Kim, Chang-hwan Moon, Eun-seok Shim, and Jo-heum Lee, who participated in this exhibition, experienced confusion and anxiety as they experienced physical and mental isolation from their daily lives that had changed due to the corona pandemic this year. Like Nietzsche, who explored “what kind of change he went through and became a man (Wie man wird, was man ist.)” in spite of mental disorder, through this exhibition, the artists reflect on their work in the twisted daily life, and We try to overcome the confusion by presenting an artistic reinterpretation.','https://artmuse.gwangju.go.kr/upload/pj/PJ_EXHIBIT/1635308015677067.jpg'),(8,'','Iksan 10 Million Chrysanthemum Festival','Iksan city area','2021-10-20 00:00:00','2021-11-14 00:00:00','As the nation\'s largest chrysanthemum garden where the city and agriculture coexist, it is a festival full of various things to see, enjoy, and eat, such as colorful and colorful chrysanthemums and chrysanthemum bonsai, new varieties exhibition, urban agriculture hall, cultural performances, and music fountains.',''),(9,'','Jeolla Gamyeong is back','Jeolla Gamyeong area','2021-10-08 00:00:00','2021-12-26 00:00:00','The Return of Jeolla Gamyeong Program is an outdoor room based on historical facts and storytelling of the history of Joseon and the daily life of the observers at \"Jeolla Gamyeong',' the best governing institution that encompasses the politics'),(10,'','Sense Garden: When the night falls, the light rises','National Asia Culture Center Gwangju The outdoor sky garden, open courtyard area of the Asia Culture Center','2021-09-01 00:00:00','2021-12-31 00:00:00','Let\'s take a walk through the sensuous garden at night and enjoy leisure and freedom with works of art. You can meet media art and music in the sensory garden where you can feel sight, hearing, smell and touch, as well as poetry by Ha Sang-wook, fragrant soap sculptures, emerald-colored fireflies, and colorful moonlight.','https://www.acc.go.kr/resources/upload/1228/20211014161438_603134368.gif'),(11,'','Sense Garden: When the night falls, the light rises','National Asia Culture Center Gwangju The outdoor sky garden, open courtyard area of the Asia Culture Center','2021-09-01 00:00:00','2021-12-31 00:00:00','Let\'s take a walk through the sensuous garden at night and enjoy leisure and freedom with works of art. You can meet media art and music in the sensory garden where you can feel sight, hearing, smell and touch, as well as poetry by Ha Sang-wook, fragrant soap sculptures, emerald-colored fireflies, and colorful moonlight.','https://www.acc.go.kr/resources/upload/1228/20211014161438_603134368.gif'),(12,'','Jindo Saturday Folklore Tour','Local Cultural Center Grand Performance Hall','2021-03-01 00:00:00','2021-12-31 00:00:00','Jindo Saturday Folklore Tour\'s permanent performance on Jindo Island, designated as Korea\'s first special folk culture and arts zone, is held every Saturday at 2 pm at the Jindo Local Cultural Center grand performance hall. This is to provide opportunities for cultural and artistic experience, enjoyment, and sights to domestic and foreign tourists visiting Jindo by attracting 10,000 people and transforming Jindo-gun\'s excellent intangible cultural heritage into a stage play.','https://search.pstatic.net/common/?src=http%3A%2F%2Fblogfiles.naver.net%2FMjAyMDEyMTBfMjAy%2FMDAxNjA3NTg4ODY4NDc1.mzAsLYmnBqMeXHdKdNc1PBIJHlxnSzYHQb17COsJ4pwg.MQ4kYIpsR4u-Q7G5DBts2SqV3-mDPcdwZMA3aWdfTGIg.JPEG.yeogiyou%2F1.jpg&type=sc960_832');
